    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-03T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="206"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/9–348: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Certain
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Missions</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d206fn1">Sent to United States diplomatic missions in
                        Austria, Iceland, Portugal, Switzerland, Turkey, and France.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-03T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 3, 1948—11 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Notwithstanding <gloss target="#t_cirtel1">cirtel</gloss> Aug 20,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d206fn2">See footnote 3 to circular telegram, July 8, 1948, 8 a. m.,
                            <ref target="#pg_926">p. 926</ref>.</note> following <gloss
                        target="#t_ERP1">ERP</gloss> countries have not accepted invitation
                    participate forthcoming tariff negotiations looking their early accession <gloss
                        target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>: Austria, Iceland, Portugal, Switzerland,
                    Turkey. Dept will not take further steps now press these Govts agree participate
                    spring negotiations. <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> concurs.</p>
                <p>Sent missions countries mentioned above and Paris for Harriman.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
